<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>take one’s hour • take one’s time</xh5><p> <i>take one’s hour—</i>use an approximate period of time that one may need: Almost everything should be covered in the writing guide, so <u>take your hour</u> or two, and read it.</p><p> <i>take one’s time—</i>1. not hurry; be slow and careful: Just <u>take your time</u> and tell me clearly what happened. 2. <i>(sarcastic)</i> use more time than is reasonable: The workmen are certainly <u>taking their time</u> over the job.</p><p> <i>See also: take the time / take time.</i></p> </entry>
